    "description": "Civil Procedure is the field that explains how lawsuits move through court: who can sue, where a case can be heard, what papers must be filed, how evidence is exchanged, and how judges manage the process. It matters anywhere people, businesses, and governments turn conflict into a legal case. The field is full of practical ideas about fairness, deadlines, strategy, and the hidden rules that shape outcomes before anyone reaches a verdict. It also leads to work in litigation, clerking, legal practice, public service, and policy. This chapter gives you a clear map of the courtroom process so the rest of the course has a place to fit.",
    "title": "How lawsuits move through court"
  },
